Author: adi_onysus
Content:
When you feel the muscles are completely drained, it is literally drained of sugar in the shape of glycogen, so it‚Äôs basically a sponge ready to absorb sugar quickly. And in this case, consumption of simple sugar is well-needed to refill glycogen storage

Protein should also be consumed after exercise, especially when after drinking sugary drinks since you‚Äôll have plenty of insulin roaming around waiting for nutrients to be transported

When you consume simple sugars, insulin will also spike. When in the context of a sedentary lifestyle, constant insulin spike is bad, but in the context of exercise, your cells REALLY need those nutrients, so insulin spike post-workout is absolutely fine
